title: Configure, disable logs redaction

question: Currently, this is how I enable Azure SDK logging in my code:

```csharp
private static void EnableAzureSdkLogging(WebApplication app)
{
    var logger = app.Services.GetRequiredService<ILogger<Program>>();
    var listener = new AzureEventSourceListener(
        (args, message) =>
        {
            if (logger.IsEnabled(LogLevel.Trace) &&
                args.EventSource.Name.StartsWith("Azure-Core", StringComparison.OrdinalIgnoreCase))
            {
                switch (args.EventId)
                {
                    case 1:
                    case 5:
                    {
                        logger.LogTrace("Azure-Core Event: {name}.AzureSDK, Message: {body}", args.EventId, message);
                        break;
                    }
                }
            }
        },
        EventLevel.Informational);
    app.Lifetime.ApplicationStopping.Register(listener.Dispose);
}
```

what results in a row like this in the logs:

| name | body | headers | uri |
| --- | --- | --- | --- |
| Azure.Core | Request [c02609c9-e49b-44d4-94c4-32b265f500c6] DELETE https://atsdevwus2tcfg.blob.core.windows.net/t... | x-ms-delete-snapshots:include x-ms-version:2026-04-06 Accept:application/xml x-ms-client-request-... | https://atsdevwus2tcfg.blob.core.windows.net/throttle/atsgsolympiadevwestus22026061852424532794e166/... |

as you can see, many values are redacted. But none of them need to be. I wonder how to configure or simplify disable that?

I found this article: [azure-sdk-for-net/sdk/core/Azure.Core/samples/Diagnostics.md at main · Azure/azure-sdk-for-net](https://github.com/Azure/azure-sdk-for-net/blob/main/sdk/core/Azure.Core/samples/Diagnostics.md)
but all it says is this:

```csharp
SecretClientOptions options = new SecretClientOptions()
{
    Diagnostics =
    {
        LoggedHeaderNames = { "*" },
        LoggedQueryParameters = { "*" }
    }
};
```

without mentioning where to pass the resulting `options`. Please advise

ground_truth:
`AzureEventSourceListener` only forwards logs; it does not control redaction. To un-redact Azure SDK request logs, configure the specific client's options at construction time. The `SecretClientOptions` sample is generic; for Blob Storage use `BlobClientOptions` and pass it into `BlobServiceClient` / `BlobContainerClient` / `BlobClient`:

```csharp
var options = new BlobClientOptions
{
    Diagnostics =
    {
        IsLoggingContentEnabled = true,
        LoggedHeaderNames = { "*" },
        LoggedQueryParameters = { "*" }
    }
};

var client = new BlobServiceClient(new Uri(endpoint), credential, options);
```

If you register clients with dependency injection, configure that registration's options instead:

```csharp
builder.Services.AddAzureClients(azure =>
{
    azure.AddBlobServiceClient(new Uri(endpoint))
         .ConfigureOptions(options =>
         {
             options.Diagnostics.IsLoggingContentEnabled = true;
             options.Diagnostics.LoggedHeaderNames.Add("*");
             options.Diagnostics.LoggedQueryParameters.Add("*");
         });
});
```

Keep your `AzureEventSourceListener`, but move the redaction settings to client construction time.

